MAP_FROM_ARRAYS (array1, array2)

Returns a map created from an array1 and *array2. Note that the lengths of two arrays should be the same

```
> SELECT map_from_arrays(array(1.0, 3.0), array('2', '4'));
 {1.0:"2",3.0:"4"} 
```

STR_TO_MAP(string[, stringDelimiter[, keyValueDelimiter]])

Returns a map after splitting the string into key/value pairs using delimiters. Default delimiters are ',' for stringDelimiter and ':' for keyValueDelimiter BothpairDelimandkeyValueDelimare treated as regular expressions.

```
Examples:

> SELECT str_to_map('a:1,b:2,c:3', ',', ':');

- {"a":"1","b":"2","c":"3"}

> SELECT str_to_map('a');
 {"a":null} 
```

MAP_FROM_ARRAYS (array1, array2)

Returns a map created from an array1 and *array2. Note that the lengths of two arrays should be the same

> SELECT map_from_arrays(array(1.0, 3.0), array('2', '4'));
 {1.0:"2",3.0:"4"}

array_compact(array) - Removes null values from the array.
Examples:

> SELECT array_compact(array(1, 2, 3, null));

[1,2,3]

> SELECT array_compact(array("a", "b", "c"));

 ["a","b","c"]
